---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Why 413Septic.com exists — a local resource for western Massachusetts homeowners navigating septic systems, regulations, and contractors."
>
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 py-10">
    <Breadcrumbs crumbs={[
      { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
      { label: 'About' },
    ]} />

    <h1 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 mb-6">About 413Septic.com</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-sm prose-a:text-forest-700 max-w-none text-gray-700 space-y-4">
      <p>
        I built this site because I couldn't find it when I needed it.
      </p>
      <p>
        Like a lot of people in western Massachusetts, I own a home with a septic system. And like most
        homeowners, I inherited a system I knew almost nothing about — when it was last pumped, whether
        my town had any local regulations beyond state Title 5, or which contractors actually served
        my area versus which ones would never return my calls.
      </p>
      <p>
        When I started researching, I found the same frustrations over and over: Board of Health websites
        that hadn't been updated in years, regulation documents buried in meeting minutes from 2009,
        contractor listings on national sites that were outdated or just wrong, and no single place
        that put it all together for Franklin County.
      </p>
      <p>
        So I built that place.
      </p>
      <p>
        413Septic.com covers all 26 towns in Franklin County, with information on local regulations,
        Board of Health contacts, and contractors who actually serve the area. The contractor listings
        are sourced from multiple independent directories and cross-verified — not just scraped from
        one place. The regulation pages are sourced directly from town documents and BOH websites,
        with dates and sources cited.
      </p>
      <p>
        I'm not a septic professional. I'm a web designer who went down a research rabbit hole and
        decided to make something useful out of it. The site is built to help homeowners make informed
        decisions — not to generate leads or pretend to be something it isn't.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you're a contractor and want to claim or update your listing, <a href="/contact/">reach out</a>.
        If you find an error, please tell me — this information matters and I want it to be right.
      </p>
      <p>
        — Zac, <a href="https://banaswebdesign.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Banas Web Design</a>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8 p-4 bg-earth-50 border border-earth-200 rounded-lg text-sm text-gray-600">
      <p class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-1">Questions or corrections?</p>
      <p>Use the <a href="/contact/" class="text-forest-700 hover:underline">contact form</a> or email directly. I read everything.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
